  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Quantity Surveyor",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Perform Quantity Take-off and understanding of requirements in each tender that meet client’s expectation.</li>\n  <li>Evaluate and recommend the award of construction contracts.</li>\n  <li>Participate in on-site and consultant meetings, collaborating with clients, architects, and associate consultants for effective project administration.</li>\n  <li>Assist the Project Manager in all contractual and costing matters, ensuring compliance with procurement procedures.</li>\n  <li>Prepare valuations, pricing, and agreements of contract variations, process claims, and monitor project cash flows.</li>\n  <li>Verify subcontractors’/suppliers’ monthly progressive claims, obtain approval, and prepare payment certificates.</li>\n  <li>Prepare and submit monthly payment claims to project owner.</li>\n  <li>Review and revise contract terms and conditions as necessary.</li>\n  <li>Call for quotations, prepare, and compile tender documents.</li>\n  <li>Evaluate tender submissions and prepare tender clarification questions.</li>\n  <li>Attend tender interviews as required.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Possess at least a Diploma, Advanced/Higher/Graduate Diploma, Bachelor's Degree, Post Graduate Diploma, Professional Degree in Quantity Surveying, Civil Engineering, or equivalent.</li>\n  <li>Minimum of <strong>5 years</strong> of relevant experience in the construction or built environment industry.</li>\n  <li><strong>Previous experience in pre- and post-contract work for HDB BTO projects are preferred.</strong></li>\n  <li>Highly motivated individual with strong confidence, drive, and exceptional interpersonal skills.</li>\n  <li>Well-organized and able to perform under pressure.</li>\n</ul>",
